dc:description: Gazda: Ptolemaic king. White marble perhaps completed in stucco, metal crowning ornament missing.
Gazda: The style of the royal portrait, with its softly modeled surfaces and blurred details, recalls that of 4th century Greek sculptor Praxiteles.
